Mr David Nonyana, overseer at Middelburg Dam has announced that a dam level reading of 96.2% was measured and that the level keeps rising with a strong intake.
The sluice gates will be opened today (Tuesday) at 18:00 and residents are warned to avoid the banks of the Klein Olifants River as water levels are expected to rise. Middelburg has experienced a healthy level of rainfall throughout the week resulting in certain areas experiencing mild flooding. A video was circulated of the Amora Bird Park in Gholfsig where water flushed through the park during Mondayâ€™s rainfall. 